<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="W" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Weary2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Weary,</orth> vb. 1) to fatigue, to tire: <bibl n="shak. luc 737" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 737</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. luc 737" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 737</bibl> <bibl n="shak. luc 737" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 737</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tmp 3.1.19" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. III, 1, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.343" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 343</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.1.108" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 1, 108</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.4.385" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 385</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.112" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 4, 112</bibl> (Ff <emph>--ed head,</emph> Qq <emph>weary neck</emph>). <bibl n="shak. jc 4.3.200" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. IV, 3, 200</bibl>. cf. <emph>Day-wearied, War-wearied.</emph><lb />2) to make impatient of continuance; and hence to harass by any thing irksome: <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.4.126" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. II, 4, 126</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 1.1.2" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 1, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.4.38" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 4, 38</bibl> (later Ff <emph>wearying,</emph> F<hi rend="sub">1</hi> <emph>wearing</emph>). <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.2.164" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 164</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 5.2.56" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 56</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.342" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 342</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.5.94" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 5, 94</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>